# Incident Reports

## RPC Downtime on March 6

The testnet's RPC servers went down. A curious user found that we left open the `debug_traceCall` method and crafted a query that uses a large amount of memory on the server, basically by causing allocation of a really long string. By spamming such queries, the user was able to cause the server to run out of memory. This is indeed an interesting test case we did not think of.

Our monitors caught the out-of-memory errors quickly after the incident happened and automatically attempted to restart the RPC nodes. Unfortunately, since the user was still sending these queries, RPC nodes went down again soon after the restart. The engineers started working on the issue about 1.5 hours after the incident started. Identifying the root cause and implemeting fixes took another 1.5 hours.  

During the incident, block production continued normally. The problematic RPC methods have been blocked.
